WEBVTT

00:12.012 --> 00:13.556
[Ray]
Previously on  Ray Donovan...

00:13.556 --> 00:15.225
It's all prearranged.

00:15.225 --> 00:18.061
All we got to do is go in,
cut the safe, get the money.

00:18.061 --> 00:20.396
Gone in 15 minutes, tops.

00:20.396 --> 00:22.022
- Fuck you!
- [Sylvie] No, no!

00:22.022 --> 00:24.191
Do it.

00:24.191 --> 00:26.652
- Now drop the fucking gun!
- [yells]

00:26.652 --> 00:28.362
[yells]

00:28.362 --> 00:31.073
♪ dramatic music ♪

00:31.073 --> 00:34.076
[Marisol] Me and my brother,
Hector, we love each other.

00:34.076 --> 00:35.870
I mean, in love.

00:35.870 --> 00:39.039
It was--it was killing me,
all the secrecy.

00:39.039 --> 00:40.958
And I think it's killing
my brother.

00:40.958 --> 00:45.130
Maybe y-you'd like to have
dinner with me sometime.

00:45.130 --> 00:46.922
How about a drink instead?

00:46.922 --> 00:48.466
Yeah, that's even better.

00:48.466 --> 00:51.302
This footage from the port
of the dead girl,

00:51.302 --> 00:53.679
of Ivan going in and not
coming out--

00:53.679 --> 00:55.055
You killed him.

00:55.055 --> 00:56.265
Yes.

00:56.265 --> 00:57.683
So you  make it
your business

00:57.683 --> 01:00.103
to commit suicide
and take me down with you.

01:00.103 --> 01:01.061
♪♪♪

01:01.061 --> 01:02.480
[Avi] Okay, okay, okay.

01:02.480 --> 01:05.191
[men grunting, yelling]

01:05.191 --> 01:08.319
[Sonia] If it comes down to it,
don't deal with Dmitri.

01:08.319 --> 01:11.655
Disappear,
or he'll kill you.

01:11.655 --> 01:13.240
- [phone ringing]
- Yeah?

01:13.240 --> 01:14.492
[Avi coughing]

01:14.492 --> 01:17.077
[moaning]

01:17.077 --> 01:18.829
Avi?

01:18.829 --> 01:21.624
Bring me my niece,

01:21.624 --> 01:23.501
or I kill your Jew.

01:23.501 --> 01:28.506
♪♪♪

01:40.434 --> 01:43.479
♪ ominous music ♪

01:43.479 --> 01:48.484
♪♪♪

01:52.696 --> 01:54.198
There he is.

01:54.198 --> 01:59.203
♪♪♪

02:02.540 --> 02:04.625
They do anything to Avi,
I'm gonna fucking kill them.

02:04.625 --> 02:08.171
♪♪♪

02:08.171 --> 02:10.340
Wait.
Shouldn't I go with her?

02:10.340 --> 02:12.342
[breathes deeply]

02:12.342 --> 02:14.177
Just do what I told you to do.

02:14.177 --> 02:16.346
♪♪♪

02:16.346 --> 02:18.138
Wait for her signal.

02:18.138 --> 02:19.139
Okay.

02:19.139 --> 02:23.352
♪♪♪

02:23.352 --> 02:24.562
Hell, yeah.

02:24.562 --> 02:29.567
♪♪♪

02:46.251 --> 02:47.459
[Jacob]
These pieces stay.

02:47.459 --> 02:48.836
They don't matter.

02:48.836 --> 02:50.255
Only take the ones
that I selected.

02:50.255 --> 02:51.839
Careful with
the Strasser, okay?

02:51.839 --> 02:53.299
For God's sake, be careful.

02:53.299 --> 02:54.341
- Yes, sir.

02:54.341 --> 02:56.385
- Platz goes in last.
- Last.

02:56.385 --> 02:57.970
Slow down.

02:57.970 --> 03:01.599
Do it correctly.
Platz goes in last.

03:01.599 --> 03:02.600
[grunts]

03:02.600 --> 03:07.605
♪♪♪

03:08.689 --> 03:10.816
Call your friends in here.

03:10.816 --> 03:11.817
Now.

03:11.817 --> 03:14.278
Mr. Ruznov.

03:14.278 --> 03:16.030
Mr. Krupiev.

03:16.030 --> 03:21.035
♪♪♪

03:28.376 --> 03:29.793
All I want's my guy.

03:29.793 --> 03:32.046
[engine rumbling]

03:32.046 --> 03:37.051
♪♪♪

03:41.555 --> 03:44.767
[gun cocks]

03:44.767 --> 03:48.438
You shoot me, you'll never see
that truck again.

03:48.438 --> 03:50.230
Lower your weapons.

03:50.230 --> 03:53.484
Lower your weapons.

03:53.484 --> 03:56.236
You tell your boss,
he lays a finger on Avi,

03:56.236 --> 03:57.946
I'll burn his fucking art.

03:57.946 --> 04:02.868
♪♪♪

04:16.757 --> 04:19.760
[tires squealing]

04:27.226 --> 04:29.269
[truck door closes]

04:35.360 --> 04:37.445
[engine turning over]

04:45.828 --> 04:49.457
[keys jingling]

04:53.752 --> 04:54.753
[Ray]
You all right?

04:58.466 --> 04:59.758
Yeah.

04:59.758 --> 05:01.677
Did you get the art?

05:01.677 --> 05:03.471
Yeah, we got all of it.

05:06.890 --> 05:08.016
That's good.

05:16.024 --> 05:17.609
You should've killed her.

05:17.609 --> 05:21.405
♪ low instrumental music ♪

05:21.405 --> 05:24.158
Wouldn't have made
a difference.

05:24.158 --> 05:29.163
♪♪♪

05:46.096 --> 05:48.516
Dad?

05:48.516 --> 05:50.560
Are you okay?

05:50.560 --> 05:53.228
♪♪♪

05:53.228 --> 05:54.605
I need you to stay close
to your mother

05:54.605 --> 05:55.981
and your brother today.

05:55.981 --> 05:58.776
♪♪♪

05:58.776 --> 06:01.236
Will you do that for me?

06:01.236 --> 06:06.241
♪♪♪

06:06.241 --> 06:07.535
What?

06:07.535 --> 06:12.122
♪♪♪

06:12.122 --> 06:13.541
I love you.

06:13.541 --> 06:15.876
♪♪♪

06:15.876 --> 06:17.920
You know that, right?

06:17.920 --> 06:19.589
Yeah.

06:19.589 --> 06:24.594
♪♪♪

06:40.108 --> 06:42.528
- Morning.
- Morning.

06:47.616 --> 06:49.494
Not that it matters,

06:49.494 --> 06:51.411
but I hope you don't think
I do this kind of shit a lot.

06:51.411 --> 06:54.164
No, no. I don't--
I don't think anything.

06:54.164 --> 06:55.458
I just...

06:55.458 --> 06:56.959
[sighs]

06:56.959 --> 06:59.628
I just think
you're fucking beautiful.

07:03.340 --> 07:06.343
[cell phone beeps]

07:10.598 --> 07:13.559
Listen...

07:13.559 --> 07:16.854
there's s-something
you should know about me.

07:16.854 --> 07:19.940
What?

07:19.940 --> 07:21.608
[sighs]

07:21.608 --> 07:25.571
About a year ago, I was serving
time for armed robbery.

07:28.365 --> 07:30.660
Not long after I got out...

07:32.411 --> 07:34.288
[cheek clicks]

07:34.288 --> 07:36.456
I got shot,

07:36.456 --> 07:38.792
and I was lying in the ICU,

07:38.792 --> 07:41.587
and I could feel my body
just letting go.

07:41.587 --> 07:46.091
You know?
It's--it was just giving up.

07:46.091 --> 07:49.720
But I could hear this voice
in my head,

07:49.720 --> 07:52.472
and it said,

07:52.472 --> 07:56.435
"After the pain...

07:56.435 --> 07:58.937
there's love."

07:58.937 --> 08:01.857
♪ light instrumental music ♪

08:01.857 --> 08:04.026
♪♪♪

08:04.026 --> 08:05.485
There's coffee in the kitchen

08:05.485 --> 08:07.362
and probably some yogurt
in the refrigerator.

08:07.362 --> 08:08.822
Yeah.
Thanks.

08:08.822 --> 08:10.490
I'm late for work.

08:10.490 --> 08:11.617
♪♪♪

08:11.617 --> 08:14.870
[door creaks open, closes]

08:14.870 --> 08:18.415
[breathing heavily]

08:18.415 --> 08:23.462
♪♪♪

08:24.713 --> 08:28.216
[indistinct chatter]

08:36.683 --> 08:40.812
[cell phone beeping]

08:40.812 --> 08:42.481
[line trilling]

08:42.481 --> 08:43.815
[Maureen] Did you leave
something at my place?

08:43.815 --> 08:46.151
No, no.
It's nothing like that.

08:46.151 --> 08:48.946
Listen, the fight
I'm working on--

08:48.946 --> 08:51.156
it's in a month's time,

08:51.156 --> 08:52.824
and the night before,
there's a big dinner

08:52.824 --> 08:55.494
for the fighters
and their teams, you know?

08:55.494 --> 08:56.912
It's real fancy.

08:56.912 --> 09:00.499
There's, uh, big dresses,
penguin suits--

09:00.499 --> 09:02.042
[Maureen]
You asking me?

09:04.503 --> 09:06.088
You don't got
to tell me now, you know?

09:06.088 --> 09:08.674
Just--just think about it.
[locker clatters]

09:08.674 --> 09:11.719
[Hector] Then you shouldn't
have lit a fucking fire!

09:11.719 --> 09:14.471
- What's going on?
- [Punch] Talking to his sister.

09:14.471 --> 09:16.640
[Marisol] It was so ugly
in jail, Hector.

09:16.640 --> 09:19.518
People knew who I was.
They wanted to hurt me.

09:21.103 --> 09:23.438
I took care of that priest,

09:23.438 --> 09:26.149
and you fucking took care
of our daddy.

09:26.149 --> 09:28.527
I don't got time for this.
I told you.

09:28.527 --> 09:30.195
[Marisol]
We saved each other.

09:30.195 --> 09:33.490
After that, you weren't
my little brother anymore.

09:33.490 --> 09:34.533
You were mine.

09:34.533 --> 09:36.118
It's the past, Marisol.

09:36.118 --> 09:37.786
It don't matter no more.

09:37.786 --> 09:39.413
[Marisol] You keep telling me
that, Hector.

09:39.413 --> 09:41.498
You keep saying that shit.

09:41.498 --> 09:43.709
It fucking matters.

09:46.086 --> 09:47.129
[cell phone beeps]

09:47.129 --> 09:49.297
Hey, let's get to work.

09:51.883 --> 09:53.761
Yo, you were out all night
with that lady cop?

09:53.761 --> 09:55.512
Yeah.
You're conditioning today.

09:55.512 --> 09:57.764
Yo, she make you keep your hands
where you can see 'em?

09:57.764 --> 09:59.141
Hey, what,
are you a comedian now?

09:59.141 --> 10:01.018
Do me a favor--
go and run six miles

10:01.018 --> 10:03.771
and see if you're still laughing
when you get back.

10:03.771 --> 10:05.605
Hector!

10:06.940 --> 10:08.275
Footwork this morning.

10:08.275 --> 10:10.610
No gloves.
Let's keep focused.

10:10.610 --> 10:12.446
You got four weeks
to get yourself ready.

10:12.446 --> 10:13.822
Huh?
Get your shit together.

10:13.822 --> 10:16.283
And that means no more calls
from your sister.

10:16.283 --> 10:17.617
Understood?

10:22.456 --> 10:23.874
Terry, there's no point
in telling him

10:23.874 --> 10:25.625
what the rules are
when he gets like this.

10:25.625 --> 10:27.210
- It's a waste of time.
- Oh, yeah?

10:27.210 --> 10:29.797
Well, I'm doing my job.
What about you?

10:29.797 --> 10:32.382
He's all yours, boss.

10:32.382 --> 10:36.094
[indistinct chatter on TV]

10:36.094 --> 10:37.763
No.
Come on, Maria.

10:37.763 --> 10:39.639
- Just take the bottle for me.
- [baby fussing]

10:39.639 --> 10:41.850
We can't do that other thing.

10:41.850 --> 10:44.686
- Phone's for you.
- Who is it?

10:44.686 --> 10:47.731
Uh, uh, It's some lady
from your doctor's office.

10:47.731 --> 10:50.442
Just tell her
I'll call her back.

10:50.442 --> 10:51.736
You should take it.

10:52.903 --> 10:55.906
[baby fussing]

10:57.657 --> 10:59.702
Hello?

10:59.702 --> 11:03.371
[baby grunting]

11:03.371 --> 11:04.832
Yeah.

11:04.832 --> 11:06.625
I, uh...

11:06.625 --> 11:08.794
I already talked
to her about that.

11:12.464 --> 11:14.674
That won't be necessary.

11:14.674 --> 11:17.887
No, I won't be
coming in for that.

11:17.887 --> 11:20.680
No.
That's right.

11:22.015 --> 11:23.141
Thank you.

11:23.141 --> 11:25.060
- Bye.
- [phone beeps]

11:25.060 --> 11:26.771
Are you okay?

11:29.439 --> 11:32.317
Yeah.
I'm fine.

11:32.317 --> 11:35.070
♪ ominous music ♪

11:35.070 --> 11:37.697
Bridge, just go
to your room right now.

11:37.697 --> 11:39.491
What is it?

11:39.491 --> 11:41.451
Just go.

11:41.451 --> 11:43.495
- I need to talk to your dad.
- [phone beeping]

11:43.495 --> 11:46.832
♪♪♪

11:46.832 --> 11:49.543
- [breathes deeply]
- [line trilling]

11:49.543 --> 11:51.711
Ray?

11:51.711 --> 11:52.796
Hey, Abby.

11:52.796 --> 11:55.757
There's somebody outside...

11:55.757 --> 11:56.758
in a car.

11:56.758 --> 11:58.552
Daryll will keep an eye on him.

11:58.552 --> 11:59.886
Just keep the kids upstairs.

11:59.886 --> 12:01.555
I'll get back there
as soon as I can.

12:01.555 --> 12:03.640
[indistinct chatter]

12:03.640 --> 12:05.851
♪♪♪

12:05.851 --> 12:08.019
All right.
Ten minutes.

12:08.019 --> 12:11.565
♪♪♪

12:11.565 --> 12:13.901
I need you
to shut down the gym.

12:13.901 --> 12:16.486
- Why?
- There's trouble, Terry.

12:16.486 --> 12:19.865
- What, the Russians?
- Yeah.

12:19.865 --> 12:21.283
Well, we're fighting
for the championship

12:21.283 --> 12:22.827
in four weeks' time.

12:22.827 --> 12:24.911
- You're not safe here.
- Are you kidding me?

12:24.911 --> 12:27.747
I got security and media coming
through the fucking yin-yang.

12:27.747 --> 12:29.166
They're not gonna come
through those doors

12:29.166 --> 12:30.959
and shooting up shit
in front of those cameras.

12:30.959 --> 12:33.753
[whispering] Terry, please, it's
better for me if you lay low.

12:33.753 --> 12:35.923
Hey, I've been laying low
my whole life, Ray.

12:35.923 --> 12:37.799
I'm not gonna
lay low no more.

12:37.799 --> 12:39.134
Fuck  'em.

12:39.134 --> 12:42.762
♪♪♪

12:42.762 --> 12:44.598
On the balls of your feet.
Come on, come on.

12:44.598 --> 12:46.766
On the balls of your feet.
Stamp out the cigarette, yeah?

12:46.766 --> 12:49.603
- [knock on door]
- [normal voice] Bunch.

13:05.076 --> 13:08.330
[Bunchy groans]

13:14.920 --> 13:16.588
What the fuck is this?

13:19.132 --> 13:20.926
Huh?

13:20.926 --> 13:22.802
[inhales deeply]

13:25.805 --> 13:28.808
[exhales deeply]

13:28.808 --> 13:31.561
We went to Primm with Mick.

13:32.812 --> 13:33.980
You what?

13:37.817 --> 13:39.862
It was a fucking
bloodbath, Ray.

13:39.862 --> 13:42.155
[sighs]

13:42.155 --> 13:46.451
His girl got it
in her heart.

13:46.451 --> 13:47.827
Fucking went nuts,

13:47.827 --> 13:51.248
shot up the whole place,
killed everybody.

13:51.248 --> 13:54.251
♪ solemn music ♪

13:54.251 --> 13:59.297
♪♪♪

14:02.425 --> 14:04.386
Your daughter's in my house.

14:04.386 --> 14:07.597
♪♪♪

14:07.597 --> 14:09.015
I need you there, Bunch.

14:11.351 --> 14:13.896
Put your fucking clothes on
and get over there now.

14:13.896 --> 14:18.901
♪♪♪

14:34.207 --> 14:36.084
[sighs]

14:36.084 --> 14:38.503
Are you out
of your fucking mind?

14:40.089 --> 14:41.256
Huh?

14:43.883 --> 14:46.053
You killed Bill Primm?

14:49.764 --> 14:52.934
I-I got your cut put aside--
a million dollars.

14:52.934 --> 14:54.561
You earned it.

14:54.561 --> 14:57.106
Why the fuck would you
take Bunchy with you?

14:59.858 --> 15:01.651
You want your cut or not?

15:04.029 --> 15:05.655
Give it to Bunch.

15:05.655 --> 15:07.866
He's gonna need it
for his fucking lawyers.

15:07.866 --> 15:08.867
Ray.

15:15.707 --> 15:18.835
It was just a situation,
you know.

15:18.835 --> 15:20.963
I stole the money from him.

15:20.963 --> 15:23.882
He stole it back from us.

15:23.882 --> 15:26.509
He got his four million
from the insurance,

15:26.509 --> 15:29.138
and I just wanted mine.

15:29.138 --> 15:30.847
No one needed to get hurt.

15:30.847 --> 15:35.310
♪♪♪

15:35.310 --> 15:37.980
But they always do,
don't they, Mick?

15:37.980 --> 15:40.690
♪♪♪

15:40.690 --> 15:44.527
There was no reason
for her to die.

15:44.527 --> 15:46.946
That cocksucker
just shot her.

15:46.946 --> 15:48.698
[sniffles]

15:48.698 --> 15:53.703
♪♪♪

15:53.703 --> 15:57.041
When are you gonna put
your fucking family first?

15:57.041 --> 16:01.961
♪♪♪

16:10.095 --> 16:13.139
[indistinct chatter in the gym]

16:24.109 --> 16:27.154
Where you going?

16:27.154 --> 16:29.197
Calabasas.

16:29.197 --> 16:31.033
I'll come with you.

16:32.951 --> 16:35.328
Maybe you ought
to ask Ray first, hmm?

16:35.328 --> 16:37.997
I'll just come.

16:37.997 --> 16:40.417
Sure. Why not?

16:40.417 --> 16:43.336
You do whatever the fuck you
want anyway, right, Mick?

16:53.638 --> 16:54.806
[camera shutter clicks]

16:59.269 --> 17:00.437
[camera shutter clicks]

17:03.481 --> 17:05.733
[phone ringing, beeps]

17:05.733 --> 17:06.734
Yeah.

17:06.734 --> 17:08.112
Hey, Abby was right.

17:08.112 --> 17:09.988
Sokolov has a guy
parked outside.

17:11.614 --> 17:14.159
- What's he doing?
- Just sitting there.

17:14.159 --> 17:15.285
All right, leave him.

17:15.285 --> 17:17.204
No one goes near him.

17:17.204 --> 17:18.621
All right.

17:18.621 --> 17:21.207
Oh, and I, uh, talked
to the pilots that flew Sonia.

17:21.207 --> 17:24.127
They said another plane met her
when they landed in Grenada,

17:24.127 --> 17:28.840
and she was up in the air again
before they could even refuel.

17:28.840 --> 17:31.342
- Where are they headed?
- They didn't know.

17:31.342 --> 17:32.969
All right.

17:32.969 --> 17:35.221
I'll send you
the rest of the pictures.

17:35.221 --> 17:37.223
[cell phone beeps]

17:40.226 --> 17:42.228
[baby fusses]

17:45.773 --> 17:46.774
Hey.

17:49.111 --> 17:50.820
Here she is.

17:50.820 --> 17:53.656
She missed her mama.

17:53.656 --> 17:55.658
Hi, baby.

17:55.658 --> 17:58.203
It's sweet how she's
so excited to see you.

18:02.248 --> 18:05.001
Y-you take her.

18:05.001 --> 18:06.878
No.

18:06.878 --> 18:10.048
She doesn't want me.

18:10.048 --> 18:12.342
Teresa, you have to deal
with this now.

18:12.342 --> 18:13.968
She's your baby.

18:20.184 --> 18:22.018
It's gonna be all right.

18:25.271 --> 18:26.272
Hi.

18:28.317 --> 18:32.279
[indistinct chatter,
boxing gloves thudding]

18:32.279 --> 18:34.323
What the hell's going on?

18:34.323 --> 18:36.908
She just showed up.

18:36.908 --> 18:38.493
[Jessica] She came
to our fucking house

18:38.493 --> 18:40.078
and said horrible things to me.

18:40.078 --> 18:41.287
[Hector]
She's insane!

18:41.287 --> 18:43.081
Ah, Jesus.

18:43.081 --> 18:45.917
[Jessica shouting indistinctly]

18:45.917 --> 18:48.170
[Hector]
She's fucking insane!

18:48.170 --> 18:50.129
[Jessica] Stella heard!
Stella heard everything.

18:50.129 --> 18:51.965
[Hector]
She's too young to understand.

18:51.965 --> 18:53.883
[Jessica] She understands
that you don't love me, Hector.

18:53.883 --> 18:55.260
She understands that much.

18:55.260 --> 18:57.346
[Hector] Well, you know,
I fucking love you.

18:57.346 --> 18:58.555
- I love you. I love you!
- [Jessica] No, you--

18:58.555 --> 19:01.225
Just say it one time.
Say it.

19:01.225 --> 19:02.183
[Hector] Hey, what?

19:02.183 --> 19:03.393
[Jessica] You need your sister.

19:03.393 --> 19:05.520
Hey, sweetie.

19:05.520 --> 19:08.357
Uh, are you hungry?

19:08.357 --> 19:10.275
No.

19:10.275 --> 19:11.526
You want me to show you

19:11.526 --> 19:13.320
how to wrap your hands
like your daddy?

19:13.320 --> 19:14.404
- No.
- [door opens]

19:14.404 --> 19:16.155
[Jessica]
Just have your fight.

19:16.155 --> 19:17.699
Get on with your life
and let us get on with ours.

19:17.699 --> 19:19.284
Come on, sweetie, let's go.

19:19.284 --> 19:21.245
- Wait, baby, wait.
Come here. Hug Daddy.

19:21.245 --> 19:22.453
Come here.
Hug Daddy.

19:22.453 --> 19:24.539
How you doing, baby?

19:24.539 --> 19:25.832
Okay.

19:25.832 --> 19:27.083
Come on, sweetheart.

19:27.083 --> 19:29.168
Oh, come on.

19:29.168 --> 19:33.215
Come on, please!
We--we--we can get through this.

19:33.215 --> 19:34.383
Can--

19:34.383 --> 19:35.967
Come on!

19:35.967 --> 19:37.927
Don't go!

19:37.927 --> 19:42.932
♪♪♪

19:42.932 --> 19:45.394
[door closes]

19:45.394 --> 19:47.145
[sighs]

19:49.606 --> 19:54.027
She says she's gonna take her
to Montreal.

19:54.027 --> 19:56.988
She says
she's not coming back.

19:56.988 --> 19:58.323
Get back
in the ring, you know?

19:58.323 --> 20:00.409
Work it out.
Sweat it out.

20:00.409 --> 20:03.536
♪♪♪

20:03.536 --> 20:06.080
- I'll be back in an hour.
- No, get in the ring.

20:06.080 --> 20:08.292
- It's best you stay.
- I said I'll be back.

20:08.292 --> 20:13.297
♪♪♪

20:16.966 --> 20:19.218
[door closes]

20:21.388 --> 20:23.014
[cell phone beeps, clicking]

20:23.014 --> 20:24.974
[cell phone ringing]

20:24.974 --> 20:26.434
Yeah.

20:26.434 --> 20:27.977
[Jacob] Dmitri will meet you
in an hour.

20:27.977 --> 20:29.437
Chatsworth.

20:30.688 --> 20:33.232
[cell phone beeps]

20:36.235 --> 20:38.279
So I got into
Kovitzky's cloud.

20:38.279 --> 20:41.450
I have all the gallery's
receipts and bills of sale.

20:41.450 --> 20:43.117
All right.
Stay with the art.

20:43.117 --> 20:45.287
I'll call you
if you need to move.

21:05.682 --> 21:07.684
[groans]

21:07.684 --> 21:10.269
[exhales deeply]

21:17.444 --> 21:20.488
[lemur squeaking]

21:20.488 --> 21:23.032
[speaking Russian]

21:25.743 --> 21:27.328
[speaking Russian]

21:27.328 --> 21:28.705
He's good.

21:29.831 --> 21:32.750
[dramatic music plays on laptop]

21:32.750 --> 21:34.752
[music stops]

21:37.755 --> 21:40.758
[indistinct chatter]

21:44.137 --> 21:47.932
The Kremlin Bleeds.

21:47.932 --> 21:49.308
Have you seen it?

21:49.308 --> 21:51.436
No.

21:51.436 --> 21:53.604
I love American films.

21:53.604 --> 21:56.525
I spent my childhood
in New York.

21:58.025 --> 21:59.694
Butch Kramer.

21:59.694 --> 22:01.405
[dramatic music plays on laptop]

22:01.405 --> 22:03.030
He's someone you work with?

22:03.030 --> 22:06.368
Where's Avi?

22:06.368 --> 22:09.162
Why does Mr. Kramer
employ you, Mr. Donovan?

22:09.162 --> 22:13.624
What does he do that he has
so much to be afraid of?

22:16.043 --> 22:19.506
[sighs]
You want your art back or not?

22:19.506 --> 22:21.758
[chuckles]

22:21.758 --> 22:24.886
I'm having a party tonight.

22:24.886 --> 22:26.345
Bring Butch Kramer.

22:26.345 --> 22:28.806
I want to meet him here.

22:28.806 --> 22:31.184
I want to see Avi first.

22:31.184 --> 22:33.227
You want Avi.

22:33.227 --> 22:35.354
I want to meet Butch Kramer.

22:37.732 --> 22:40.735
[dramatic music plays on laptop]

22:40.735 --> 22:45.407
♪♪♪

22:53.539 --> 22:55.625
That's for you.

22:55.625 --> 22:57.419
What is it?

22:57.419 --> 22:59.378
Record of all your sales
matched up against photos

22:59.378 --> 23:02.340
of the art
I've got on that truck.

23:02.340 --> 23:03.966
So?

23:03.966 --> 23:07.220
So that means that there
are at least ten pieces of art

23:07.220 --> 23:09.972
you sold hanging
on people's walls

23:09.972 --> 23:11.599
right here in town
that aren't real.

23:11.599 --> 23:14.393
♪ ominous music ♪

23:14.393 --> 23:17.313
Forgeries, you know.
It's just a side business.

23:17.313 --> 23:18.689
Ah, side business
you didn't tell

23:18.689 --> 23:20.024
your boss about, did you?

23:20.024 --> 23:23.402
♪♪♪

23:23.402 --> 23:26.030
I'll bring in Butch Kramer.

23:26.030 --> 23:28.866
If he gives me Avi,
he'll get his art back.

23:28.866 --> 23:30.451
♪♪♪

23:30.451 --> 23:32.578
But after that,
this needs to be over.

23:32.578 --> 23:33.788
You understand?

23:33.788 --> 23:34.872
♪♪♪

23:34.872 --> 23:37.416
[scoffs]

23:37.416 --> 23:40.419
Well, I'll ask him
to be reasonable,

23:40.419 --> 23:45.174
but truly, Mr. Donovan,
it's not in his nature.

23:45.174 --> 23:49.637
♪♪♪

23:49.637 --> 23:51.473
[engine turning over]

23:51.473 --> 23:53.891
[knocking on door]

24:05.987 --> 24:07.238
[sighs]

24:07.238 --> 24:10.199
She left.

24:10.199 --> 24:12.076
And she took Stella.

24:14.579 --> 24:16.414
Okay.

24:18.457 --> 24:20.167
Okay?

24:21.752 --> 24:23.671
I got nothing left.

24:25.631 --> 24:27.967
You got nothing left?

24:38.144 --> 24:39.896
You smell like jail.

24:42.648 --> 24:44.734
Okay.

24:44.734 --> 24:47.236
I'll run us a bath.

25:01.626 --> 25:04.671
How you doing?

25:04.671 --> 25:06.213
I've been better.

25:06.213 --> 25:08.633
[scoffs]

25:08.633 --> 25:10.552
Yeah, tell me about it.

25:14.305 --> 25:17.600
[sighs]

25:17.600 --> 25:21.228
I know this
is all on me, Abby.

25:22.438 --> 25:24.566
I know...

25:24.566 --> 25:27.569
how much
I cost us all.

25:29.487 --> 25:32.741
Don't kid yourself, Mick.

25:32.741 --> 25:35.493
This ain't all you.

25:35.493 --> 25:37.203
[scoffs]

25:37.203 --> 25:39.080
You didn't give me cancer.

25:41.082 --> 25:43.585
You didn't make
Teresa leave her baby.

25:45.378 --> 25:48.547
I done a lot of bad things.

25:48.547 --> 25:51.133
[breathes deeply]

25:52.760 --> 25:54.762
I love you, Mickey.

25:58.307 --> 25:59.767
You know why?

26:02.561 --> 26:04.146
No.

26:04.146 --> 26:06.440
'Cause I love your son.

26:08.359 --> 26:10.903
I fucking love him.

26:16.075 --> 26:18.911
First time
we were together...

26:18.911 --> 26:20.955
was in your old house.

26:24.291 --> 26:28.337
Me and Ray were laying
in that single bed of his

26:28.337 --> 26:29.797
with the chair
pushed up against the door

26:29.797 --> 26:32.591
'cause one of you
had kicked it in.

26:32.591 --> 26:34.135
Probably Ray.

26:34.135 --> 26:35.594
Probably.

26:38.597 --> 26:42.101
And we're laying there...

26:42.101 --> 26:44.603
after our first time, right?

26:47.398 --> 26:49.817
And Ray put on "Layla."

26:49.817 --> 26:52.820
You know that song?

26:52.820 --> 26:54.739
No.

26:54.739 --> 26:58.075
There's this part...

26:58.075 --> 27:01.871
when Eric Clapton
stops singing...

27:01.871 --> 27:02.997
and the guitar runs

27:02.997 --> 27:06.792
right into this
one big piano chord.

27:06.792 --> 27:08.294
[chuckles]

27:08.294 --> 27:10.171
And we're lying there.

27:10.171 --> 27:13.800
I got my head on Ray's chest,

27:13.800 --> 27:17.636
and Ray looked at me...

27:17.636 --> 27:19.055
and he said...

27:20.598 --> 27:21.974
[chuckles]

27:21.974 --> 27:24.477
"Kill me when
this song ends."

27:24.477 --> 27:25.978
W-what?

27:25.978 --> 27:27.814
[chuckles]

27:27.814 --> 27:30.816
"Slice my throat
and let me bleed out"...

27:33.360 --> 27:35.988
"'Cause it's never gonna get
any better than this."

27:40.242 --> 27:42.369
Oh.

27:42.369 --> 27:44.080
That's, uh...

27:45.832 --> 27:47.458
That's beautiful.

27:51.837 --> 27:54.215
I never knew a love
like that,

27:54.215 --> 27:56.675
not a love where I wanted
someone to slit my throat open,

27:56.675 --> 27:59.095
that's for sure.
[laughs]

28:14.652 --> 28:17.071
I want you to know
I love you, too, Abby.

28:20.866 --> 28:23.619
Best thing to happen
to this family is you.

28:29.667 --> 28:32.461
Butch, you've got the biggest
movie in the world right now.

28:32.461 --> 28:35.256
Oh, yeah, baby.
We're doing a sequel next--

28:35.256 --> 28:37.007
The Taj Mahal Bleeds.

28:37.007 --> 28:39.260
And we're gonna do it
in India, too,

28:39.260 --> 28:40.803
where the Taj Mahal is.

28:40.803 --> 28:42.721
- How exciting.
- Absolutely.

28:42.721 --> 28:44.431
I mean, it's great
for people to see India.

28:44.431 --> 28:46.100
Like, in Kremlin Bleeds,

28:46.100 --> 28:48.853
we showed people parts
of Russia they never saw.

28:48.853 --> 28:52.273
I mean, it's geo-biographical
in that way.

28:52.273 --> 28:54.733
Sorr--sorry, Diane.
Give me five minutes, okay?

28:54.733 --> 28:56.485
- Okay. Sure.
- Yeah?

29:00.197 --> 29:03.868
[indistinct chatter]

29:07.329 --> 29:09.790
What's going on, Ray?

29:09.790 --> 29:11.041
He's back.

29:11.041 --> 29:13.878
Which one?

29:13.878 --> 29:15.129
The guy, uh, who filmed you

29:15.129 --> 29:16.965
having sex
with his wife last summer.

29:16.965 --> 29:18.716
Yeah, but which one?

29:18.716 --> 29:20.927
The Internet--the guy
who posted it on the Internet.

29:20.927 --> 29:22.511
- I thought we paid him off.
- We did.

29:22.511 --> 29:23.637
But he's back.

29:23.637 --> 29:25.764
Who the fuck
does that to people?

29:25.764 --> 29:28.267
He wants you
to do him a favor.

29:28.267 --> 29:29.560
I did everything right.

29:29.560 --> 29:31.687
I went to sex rehab
in Arizona.

29:31.687 --> 29:34.481
Did you tell him that?
That I went to rehab?

29:34.481 --> 29:37.610
He doesn't seem
to care, Butch.

29:37.610 --> 29:39.195
He wants you to meet a guy
he owes money to,

29:39.195 --> 29:41.071
take a picture, shake his hand,
that sort of thing.

29:41.071 --> 29:43.532
What the fuck?

29:43.532 --> 29:44.783
Russian.
Loves your movies.

29:44.783 --> 29:46.285
He just wants to meet you.

29:46.285 --> 29:47.953
I do that, this guy
won't post the video?

29:47.953 --> 29:49.955
[clears throat]

29:54.793 --> 29:57.087
Here's the address.
Eight o'clock.

29:57.087 --> 30:00.090
You gonna stay for the rest
of the interview?

30:00.090 --> 30:01.508
No.

30:01.508 --> 30:02.968
I'm gonna cry.

30:02.968 --> 30:04.971
I always do with her.

30:04.971 --> 30:08.182
You're gonna want
to be there for that.

30:08.182 --> 30:09.808
- See you tonight.
- Hey...

30:21.445 --> 30:22.780
[grunts]

30:22.780 --> 30:24.240
[sighs]

30:24.240 --> 30:25.867
Yo, what now, coach?

30:25.867 --> 30:27.826
[aggressive hip-hop music
playing]

30:27.826 --> 30:30.037
Oh, you're...

30:30.037 --> 30:32.289
you're done for the day.

30:32.289 --> 30:33.832
What?

30:33.832 --> 30:36.502
Have a shower.
Take the rest of the day off.

30:38.128 --> 30:39.880
Hey, sounds good to me.

30:41.883 --> 30:43.092
- Punch?
- Yeah.

30:43.092 --> 30:45.344
I need
Marisol Campos' address.

30:45.344 --> 30:47.221
[chuckles]

30:47.221 --> 30:49.057
He said he'd be back
in an hour.

30:49.057 --> 30:52.226
You're forgetting, Mick,
that you work for him.

30:52.226 --> 30:54.938
You go over there,
you will be fired.

30:54.938 --> 30:58.066
Yeah? Get off the fucking phone
and give me the address.

30:58.066 --> 31:02.987
♪♪♪

31:06.782 --> 31:10.035
I don't want to fight
with you, papi.

31:10.035 --> 31:12.288
Yeah?

31:12.288 --> 31:14.916
Come.

31:14.916 --> 31:16.208
Come here.

31:22.881 --> 31:25.342
Let me help you.

31:25.342 --> 31:28.096
Give me your foot.

31:48.950 --> 31:50.951
Lift up your arms.

31:50.951 --> 31:53.954
♪ dramatic music ♪

31:53.954 --> 31:58.959
♪♪♪

32:26.403 --> 32:28.947
[exhales deeply]

32:38.957 --> 32:41.168
Mmm.

32:44.047 --> 32:45.923
[water splashing]

32:45.923 --> 32:47.633
This feels nice.

32:47.633 --> 32:52.679
♪♪♪

32:55.432 --> 32:57.017
[gasps]

33:00.021 --> 33:02.022
[gasps]

33:07.361 --> 33:09.488
- [gasps]
- [grunts]

33:10.697 --> 33:13.700
- [gasps]
- [grunting]

33:32.469 --> 33:35.472
[breathing heavily]

33:41.979 --> 33:44.273
[dog barking in the distance]

33:44.273 --> 33:47.276
[indistinct chatter]

33:56.493 --> 33:59.121
[breathing heavily]

34:00.831 --> 34:02.541
Are you all right?

34:04.877 --> 34:07.629
It's--it's bad.

34:07.629 --> 34:09.339
What is it?

34:09.339 --> 34:11.092
Marisol.

34:12.218 --> 34:13.427
♪ solemn music ♪

34:13.427 --> 34:14.761
What?

34:14.761 --> 34:16.054
♪♪♪

34:16.054 --> 34:19.016
I came over, and she...

34:19.016 --> 34:20.058
she's dead.

34:20.058 --> 34:22.144
♪♪♪

34:22.144 --> 34:23.437
Your sister?

34:23.437 --> 34:25.063
♪♪♪

34:25.063 --> 34:27.065
She killed herself, man.

34:27.065 --> 34:28.192
♪♪♪

34:28.192 --> 34:29.860
She fucking killed herself.

34:29.860 --> 34:34.907
♪♪♪

34:39.286 --> 34:41.330
[line trilling]

34:41.330 --> 34:43.124
[Ray]
Yeah?

34:43.124 --> 34:46.460
You got to come over
to Marisol Campos' house.

34:46.460 --> 34:48.254
I can't right now.

34:48.254 --> 34:50.088
You got to, Ray.

34:50.088 --> 34:52.090
You got to get out here.

34:52.090 --> 34:55.093
♪♪♪

34:55.093 --> 34:57.095
[cell phone beeps]

34:57.095 --> 35:00.057
[man on TV] Unfortunately,
it's been no party for rescuers

35:00.057 --> 35:03.101
who have saved a pod
of over a dozen pilot whales

35:03.101 --> 35:06.063
after they were beached
here in the South Bay

35:06.063 --> 35:07.523
this past weekend.

35:07.523 --> 35:09.441
[continues indistinctly on TV]

35:09.441 --> 35:11.319
[whispering]
We're all gonna die.

35:11.319 --> 35:12.528
[baby grunts]

35:12.528 --> 35:14.613
[whispering]
Don't you say that.

35:14.613 --> 35:17.115
If we stay close to
your father and your brother--

35:17.115 --> 35:19.243
I know you love them.

35:19.243 --> 35:21.328
You're gonna end up dead.

35:21.328 --> 35:23.331
Maria's gonna end up dead.

35:24.331 --> 35:26.750
Don't you say that.

35:26.750 --> 35:28.919
You know it's true.

35:28.919 --> 35:31.046
We should go...

35:31.046 --> 35:33.341
me, you, and Maria.

35:33.341 --> 35:36.344
[sighs]

35:38.136 --> 35:40.889
Once Ray's back...

35:40.889 --> 35:43.308
once I know Abby
and the kids are safe...

35:46.186 --> 35:49.315
Once I know...

35:49.315 --> 35:50.566
we'll fucking leave.

35:52.693 --> 35:54.486
For good?

35:54.486 --> 35:57.364
[man on TV] ...and more recently
global warming

35:57.364 --> 35:59.199
are directly responsible...

35:59.199 --> 36:00.993
[knocking on door]

36:03.912 --> 36:05.247
It ain't pretty.

36:05.247 --> 36:07.624
She climbed into the bathtub
fucking high on drugs

36:07.624 --> 36:08.834
and passed out.

36:10.502 --> 36:13.547
♪ dismal music  ♪

36:13.547 --> 36:15.799
♪♪♪

36:15.799 --> 36:18.468
There but for the grace
of God, you know?

36:18.468 --> 36:22.139
She didn't mean
to kill herself, you know?

36:22.139 --> 36:24.350
But she did.

36:24.350 --> 36:29.104
♪♪♪

36:29.104 --> 36:31.398
Terry, you got to
get out of here.

36:31.398 --> 36:35.527
Don't mention this
to anyone.

36:35.527 --> 36:38.155
You weren't here.
You understand?

36:38.155 --> 36:40.991
- B-but it was an overdose.
- You weren't here.

36:40.991 --> 36:43.744
♪♪♪

36:43.744 --> 36:44.786
Go.

36:44.786 --> 36:47.581
You hear me?

36:47.581 --> 36:48.874
Now.

36:48.874 --> 36:53.879
♪♪♪

36:59.801 --> 37:01.970
Forgive your priest.

37:01.970 --> 37:03.722
Be a family man.

37:03.722 --> 37:05.515
Become the champion
of the world,

37:05.515 --> 37:08.477
and then the rest
will follow.

37:08.477 --> 37:12.898
And one day--one day,
the pain...

37:12.898 --> 37:15.150
it'll get better.

37:15.150 --> 37:16.818
The pain'll end.

37:19.154 --> 37:22.366
Her being dead
doesn't end anything.

37:24.409 --> 37:26.328
I-I killed her.

37:28.747 --> 37:31.458
I know.

37:31.458 --> 37:35.796
I don't want to spend
the rest of my life in prison.

37:35.796 --> 37:37.464
I want to fight.

37:37.464 --> 37:40.217
I want to be
with my daughter.

37:42.678 --> 37:46.682
I'll give you
anything you want.

37:48.767 --> 37:50.394
Good-bye, Hector.

37:50.394 --> 37:54.314
♪♪♪

37:56.024 --> 37:58.276
[sobs softly]

37:59.486 --> 38:01.405
[sniffles]

38:01.405 --> 38:04.324
[indistinct chatter,
boxing gloves thudding]

38:08.954 --> 38:11.457
[exhales deeply]

38:35.356 --> 38:37.525
How'd that go for you?

38:40.361 --> 38:42.446
Fine.

38:43.697 --> 38:46.950
Then why you drinking?

38:46.950 --> 38:49.494
I always have a drink
at the end of the day.

38:53.374 --> 38:54.750
[sighs]

38:54.750 --> 38:57.294
Like I said...

38:57.294 --> 38:59.505
welcome to Team Campos.

39:09.014 --> 39:11.016
[door opens]

39:13.268 --> 39:16.313
[door closes]

39:16.313 --> 39:19.316
[upbeat electronic music
playing]

39:19.316 --> 39:24.321
♪♪♪

39:24.321 --> 39:27.657
[indistinct chatter]

39:27.657 --> 39:29.452
[Dmitri]
Butch Kramer...

39:29.452 --> 39:30.453
[lemur squeaking]

39:30.453 --> 39:31.495
♪♪♪

39:31.495 --> 39:33.497
What an honor
it is to meet you.

39:33.497 --> 39:34.748
What's up?

39:34.748 --> 39:37.375
What a hit
Kremlin Bleeds  is, huh?

39:37.375 --> 39:38.543
Yeah, yeah.
We're doing well.

39:38.543 --> 39:41.087
I think you crossed
300 million on Friday.

39:41.087 --> 39:43.590
But listen, the toy from it
is gonna be huge.

39:43.590 --> 39:44.883
[chuckles]
Yeah.

39:44.883 --> 39:46.510
Let's go outside
and have a cigar.

39:46.510 --> 39:48.220
Well, we're actually
just leaving.

39:48.220 --> 39:51.515
Ten minutes, a cigar.

39:51.515 --> 39:52.557
Come on.

39:52.557 --> 39:57.562
♪♪♪

40:00.565 --> 40:02.359
[inhales deeply]

40:02.359 --> 40:06.029
America smells
so fucking good, Butch.

40:06.029 --> 40:07.405
[chuckles]
Yeah.

40:07.405 --> 40:11.159
That's what I always say,
more or less.

40:11.159 --> 40:13.496
[Dmitri]
Oh, I didn't mean to be rude.

40:13.496 --> 40:15.664
Butch, this is Yuri.

40:15.664 --> 40:17.749
Yuri, Butch.

40:17.749 --> 40:20.085
Yuri, my man.
Butch Kramer.

40:20.085 --> 40:21.378
Pleasure to meet you.

40:21.378 --> 40:23.421
Can you take him, you think?

40:23.421 --> 40:26.467
- What?
- [Ray] All right.

40:26.467 --> 40:27.634
You got to meet Butch Kramer.

40:27.634 --> 40:29.094
It's time
for Butch Kramer to go.

